Hi Carsten, could you tell me why you deleted this? For now, it makes error for the data import to cassandra. When camparing timeseries_latest_value_timestamp with the timestamp in a csv file, it says 

self.latest_value_timestamp <= timestamp:
  File "tslib.pyx", line 420, in pandas.tslib._Timestamp.__richcmp__ (pandas/tslib.c:7725)
TypeError: can't compare offset-naive and offset-aware datetimes
This seems to be related to https://github.com/ddsc/ddsc-core/issues/1. I'll ask Berto if he can make this part more robust. For now, you can add the line again (and please add a comment).
